    <p style="max-width: 600px; text-align: center; margin: 20px auto; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;">
        Slowness
       Mindful designing makes things slower and that is okay! The fastest response might not be the best one to design for. Instant gratification is what digital technology currently optimizes for. This results in the loss of desire, and boredom. Avoiding boredom makes us pick up our phone or open a website as soon as we have nothing to do and have to deal with a sense of existential unease. But being bored is crucial to start new fascinations and grow our sense of self-awareness. Boredom gets us into creative flow and  allows us to step into the present and connect to the world around us. Designing against speed is fuelling longing and desire; it allows boredom and elevates us to a richer life. </p>
       <p style="max-width: 600px; text-align: center; margin: 20px auto; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;"></p>        
